for trick-or-treating?

06:35.812 --> 06:38.732
Ah, frog farts.
[chuckles]

06:38.732 --> 06:40.233
It's the witching hour.

06:40.233 --> 06:43.153
That is the perfect time
to shake this city down

06:43.153 --> 06:45.655
for all the high-fructose
syrup in Reno.

06:46.614 --> 06:48.241
What do you say, Merlin?

06:48.241 --> 06:49.617
[chuckles]

06:49.617 --> 06:52.620
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

06:52.620 --> 06:57.459
<i>♪ ♪</i>

06:57.459 --> 06:59.085
[keys jingling, lock clicks]

06:59.085 --> 07:00.253
[door creaks]

07:00.253 --> 07:01.880
I'm sorry, bug.

07:01.880 --> 07:04.257
You missed Halloween,
and it's all my fault.

07:04.257 --> 07:06.760
It's okay, Dad.

07:06.760 --> 07:08.970
No.
No, it's not.

07:10.722 --> 07:12.932
I gotta have something
up my sleeve.

07:14.309 --> 07:16.436
[dove cooing]

07:16.436 --> 07:18.855
[items clattering]

07:18.855 --> 07:21.191
[frog croaks]
Huh.

07:22.484 --> 07:24.819
Okay, it's gotta be here.

07:24.819 --> 07:25.945
Ah.

07:27.030 --> 07:28.114
Ta-da.

07:30.408 --> 07:34.829
What, you wrap it caramel
and you'll have a tasty treat.

07:35.955 --> 07:37.957
We don't have any caramel.

07:44.631 --> 07:45.965
[sighs]

07:45.965 --> 07:49.386
- You okay, Dad?
- [shakily] Well, I'm sorry.

07:49.386 --> 07:51.137
I think your mother hates me.

07:53.390 --> 07:55.225
She is such a genius.

07:56.685 --> 08:01.272
But she needs showmanship
in her design.

08:01.272 --> 08:04.984
If I could just have a peek
inside her workshop,

08:04.984 --> 08:07.737
if I had any idea
what she's working on,

08:07.737 --> 08:09.239
I know I could help.

08:09.239 --> 08:11.241
I could help...

08:11.241 --> 08:13.451
bring us back together.

08:13.451 --> 08:20.625
<i>♪ ♪</i>

08:45.316 --> 08:48.236
<i>[mischievous music]</i>

08:48.236 --> 08:51.197
<i>♪ ♪</i>

08:51.197 --> 08:53.366
[exhales heavily]

08:53.366 --> 08:55.577
<i>♪ ♪</i>

08:55.577 --> 08:58.204
[metallic zip and thunk]

08:58.204 --> 09:01.207
<i>[ominous music]</i>

09:01.207 --> 09:04.252
<i>♪ ♪</i>

09:04.252 --> 09:08.214
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

09:08.214 --> 09:10.216
[monitor beeping]

09:10.216 --> 09:14.679
<i>♪ ♪</i>

09:14.679 --> 09:16.639
What happened?

09:16.639 --> 09:18.975
Hey, bug.
Don't worry.

09:18.975 --> 09:21.227
The bad news is,
the arrow's in your liver

09:21.227 --> 09:24.064
and they can't take it out
until the new liver gets here.

09:24.064 --> 09:26.608
But that's the good news.
It's on its way right now.

09:26.608 --> 09:30.195
Honey, why did you
go into my workshop?

09:30.195 --> 09:31.780
Did your father
make you do it?

09:31.780 --> 09:33.573
Jesus, Celeste.

09:33.573 --> 09:36.201
You rig a booby trap,
and you're trying to blame me?

09:36.201 --> 09:39.079
No, it was my idea.

09:39.079 --> 09:41.915
And what were you hoping
to do in there?

09:41.915 --> 09:46.753
I really just wanted
a little peek,

09:46.753 --> 09:51.132
to help you and Dad
come together.

09:54.844 --> 09:56.846
He was crying.

10:02.435 --> 10:05.772
Your father didn't even cry
the day you were born.

10:05.772 --> 10:08.483
It wasn't your idea to go in.

10:08.483 --> 10:11.277
He just made you think it was.

10:13.655 --> 10:15.699
[sighs]

10:15.699 --> 10:17.367
I'm disappointed.

10:18.326 --> 10:21.246
You should know a force
when you see one, Elizabeth.

10:23.998 --> 10:25.917
Mr. and Mrs. Abbott,

10:25.917 --> 10:27.419
a word, please.

10:36.052 --> 10:37.679
