<i>[volume lowers]</i>

15:42.359 --> 15:44.986
He's with the Boss
behind the mystery door.

15:44.986 --> 15:47.280
<i>♪ ♪</i>

15:47.280 --> 15:48.782
Anything I can help you with?

15:49.741 --> 15:50.825
No.

15:50.825 --> 15:53.203
Well, do you know
where the Holy Grail is?

15:53.203 --> 15:55.538
[chuckles]
Nope.

15:55.538 --> 15:59.876
<i>♪ ♪</i>

15:59.876 --> 16:02.879
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

16:02.879 --> 16:05.298
<i>♪ ♪</i>

16:05.298 --> 16:07.425
- [metallic bangs echo]
- Jay, it's me.

16:09.052 --> 16:10.887
Are you in there?

16:10.887 --> 16:14.265
<i>♪ ♪</i>

16:14.265 --> 16:16.393
The Algorithm
gave me a phone number,

16:16.393 --> 16:19.062
but I don't--
I'm pretty sure it's a trap.

16:19.062 --> 16:23.149
<i>♪ ♪</i>

16:23.149 --> 16:24.359
I want to talk
this through with you,

16:24.359 --> 16:25.402
but if you don't come out,

16:25.402 --> 16:27.570
I have to go somewhere else.

16:28.905 --> 16:30.448
To someone else.

16:31.825 --> 16:33.034
Jay.

16:33.034 --> 16:40.208
<i>♪ ♪</i>

16:55.098 --> 16:57.559
Will you give him this for me?

16:57.559 --> 16:59.936
Sure.
Who should I say it's from?

16:59.936 --> 17:02.188
<i>♪ ♪</i>

17:02.188 --> 17:03.690
His wife.

17:03.690 --> 17:07.235
<i>[rousing music]</i>

17:07.235 --> 17:14.409
<i>♪ ♪</i>

17:29.341 --> 17:30.467
<i>[echoing]
Hello.</i>

17:32.218 --> 17:33.720
Wiley?

17:46.316 --> 17:48.651
[hydraulics hiss]
Holy--

17:48.651 --> 17:52.489
<i>In 1917 against
the backdrop of World War I,</i>

17:52.489 --> 17:54.491
<i>an enterprising
young philanthropist...</i>

17:54.491 --> 17:55.867
How did you find me, Lizzie?

17:57.410 --> 17:58.703
I'm not Lizzie anymore.

17:59.871 --> 18:04.167
And you left the water bill
for this place

18:04.167 --> 18:05.835
in your bike.

18:05.835 --> 18:08.546
Wasn't easy, but I was able
to decode with the naked eye

18:08.546 --> 18:09.839
just the address
that's printed

18:09.839 --> 18:11.091
right here on the front.

18:11.091 --> 18:13.093
<i>Horace Erasmus
Alder Smith had a dream...</i>

18:13.093 --> 18:14.386
Shit.

18:14.386 --> 18:16.054
<i>A dream to expand
our nation's...</i>

18:16.054 --> 18:17.889
Why did you ditch my guys

18:17.889 --> 18:19.557
if you were just gonna
come here anyway?

18:19.557 --> 18:21.601
'Cause I didn't want them
to see my secret headquarters.

18:21.601 --> 18:24.145
- I don't like being mocked.
- I don't like being followed.

18:24.145 --> 18:26.815
<i>[hippo grunting]</i>

18:26.815 --> 18:30.527
<i>[tense music]</i>

18:30.527 --> 18:33.905
You talked to It,
didn't you?

18:33.905 --> 18:35.198
I talked to...

18:35.198 --> 18:37.117
That's why you were
at the elementary school.

18:37.117 --> 18:40.036
And It gave you a Quest.

18:40.036 --> 18:41.788
<i>♪ ♪</i>

18:41.788 --> 18:43.832
- Maybe.
- Uh-huh.

18:43.832 --> 18:46.960
Did It give you
some kind of clue?

18:48.253 --> 18:49.379
Queen of hearts.

18:51.006 --> 18:52.215
Of course it did.

18:53.008 --> 18:55.301
Okay, you mentioned
you and your buddies

18:55.301 --> 18:57.721
have some sort of presentation
to show me.

18:57.721 --> 18:59.389
Yeah, I need you
to put on this blindfold.

18:59.389 --> 19:00.432
- No.
- We don't let outsiders

19:00.432 --> 19:01.599
into HQ without one.

19:01.599 --> 19:03.435
- Hard pass.
- It's protocol.

19:03.435 --> 19:04.936
- It's not happening.
- Can you just put it on?

19:04.936 --> 19:05.895
Not going to.

19:05.895 --> 19:08.732
[groans]

19:08.732 --> 19:10.191
Okay, fine.

19:10.191 --> 19:12.610
I'm not closing my eyes
in a space I've never been in.

19:13.445 --> 19:15.113
What is this place anyway?

19:15.113 --> 19:17.532
<i>♪ ♪</i>

19:17.532 --> 19:19.617
Prunella, nice.

19:21.161 --> 19:22.120
[hydraulics hiss]

19:22.120 --> 19:24.247
<i>[hippo grunts]</i>

19:24.247 --> 19:25.790
Cool.

19:27.375 --> 19:30.211
Would've missed all this if I
was wearing the blindfold.

19:30.211 --> 19:34.883
<i>♪ ♪</i>

19:34.883 --> 19:36.885
It's good to see you
out of your nun costume.

19:36.885 --> 19:38.970
It's not a costume.
It's who I am.

19:38.970 --> 19:40.930
Why'd you take it off?

19:40.930 --> 19:42.766
<i>♪ ♪</i>

19:42.766 --> 19:44.142
Out of respect
for our history,

19:44.142 --> 19:45.435
I'm gonna let that one slide.

19:45.435 --> 19:47.145
You keep tugging
on my pigtails, I'm out.

19:47.145 --> 19:48.355
I don't need you.
Understand?

19:48.355 --> 19:50.065
Oh, mm-hmm.

19:50.065 --> 19:52.650
Yeah, I've understood that
for a long time now.

19:54.027 --> 19:56.279
<i>[elevator bell chimes]</i>

19:56.279 --> 19:57.655
Follow me.

19:59.157 --> 20:01.409
[indistinct chatter]

20:01.409 --> 20:03.078
<i>[dynamic music]</i>

20:03.078 --> 20:04.245
Come on.

20:04.245 --> 20:08.124
<i>♪ ♪</i>

20:08.124 --> 20:10.543
Meet... the resistance.

20:10.543 --> 20:17.717
<i>♪ ♪</i>

20:26.267 --> 20:28.186
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

20:28.186 --> 20:30.271
[indistinct chatter,
computers whirring]

20:30.271 --> 20:32.649
Hey, what was that?
Can you turn that back on?

20:32.649 --> 20:33.983
You know, Lizzie,
we don't...

20:33.983 --> 20:35.151
- Turn that back on!
- Really have time for this.

20:35.151 --> 20:36.695
I don't know which one.
There's a lot.

20:36.695 --> 20:38.113
Turn it back on.

20:38.113 --> 20:39.114
Okay, yeah.

20:39.114 --> 20:40.240
[clears throat]

20:40.240 --> 20:42.117
<i>♪ ♪</i>

20:42.117 --> 20:43.451
There, those are
the German guys

20:43.451 --> 20:45.161
that grabbed me
from the buffet.

20:45.161 --> 20:46.413
No, no, no, not Germans.

20:46.413 --> 20:48.456
Puppets for It.

20:48.456 --> 20:51.918
So if these guys
are working for It,

20:51.918 --> 20:55.171
why abduct me, question me,
and murder my horse?

20:55.171 --> 20:57.841
Simultaneous motivation
and validation for your Quest.

20:57.841 --> 20:59.634
Ah, but it hadn't
given me a Quest yet.

20:59.634 --> 21:02.470
It pre-motivated you
by threatening your horse,

21:02.470 --> 21:03.972
which pre-validated the Quest

21:03.972 --> 21:06.016
by establishing
a rival faction

21:06.016 --> 21:07.851
already searching
for the thing

21:07.851 --> 21:10.395
It wants you to search for

21:10.395 --> 21:13.314
before It even tells you

21:13.314 --> 21:15.233
what you're searching for.

21:15.233 --> 21:16.401
And what, Mr. Mustache,

21:16.401 --> 21:17.777
do you think
I'm searching for?

21:17.777 --> 21:19.779
So glad you asked.

21:19.779 --> 21:22.032
Punch up the bios
we scraped from Interpol.

21:22.032 --> 21:23.908
The Algorithm knew
you'd look these guys up,

21:23.908 --> 21:27.328
so It planted the story
that It wanted you to find.

21:27.328 --> 21:30.123
Klaus here, that's
Heinrich Mueller's grandson.

21:30.123 --> 21:32.834
And Dieter, his granddad
was also a goose-stepper.

21:32.834 --> 21:35.795
So considering
we're dealing with Nazis,

21:35.795 --> 21:38.298
I'm guessing that It

21:38.298 --> 21:41.009
has got you searching for...

21:41.009 --> 21:42.469
the Holy Grail.

21:42.469 --> 21:46.097
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

21:46.097 --> 21:47.974
Wait, but if they don't know
we're watching them,

21:47.974 --> 21:49.851
why are they still
keeping up the act?

21:49.851 --> 21:53.146
Because the act,
it's all there is.

21:53.146 --> 21:54.397
Complete commitment.

21:54.397 --> 21:56.691
These guys, they don't
break character ever.

21:56.691 --> 21:58.026
This is stupid.

21:58.026 --> 22:00.570
Why go through all this
just to pre-motivate me?

22:00.570 --> 22:01.821
Oh, don't underestimate

22:01.821 --> 22:03.406
just how stupid this gets, sweetheart.

22:03.406 --> 22:05.533
Oh, I won't...

22:05.533 --> 22:07.619
darlin'.

22:08.703 --> 22:11.331
Okay, fine.

22:11.331 --> 22:12.832
Don't believe me.

22:12.832 --> 22:14.250
I'll prove it to you.

22:15.710 --> 22:17.253
It's me.
Grab the bratwurst.

22:17.253 --> 22:19.089
Take 'em to the laundromat.

22:19.089 --> 22:19.964
[phone snaps]

22:19.964 --> 22:22.842
Whoa, that seems wasteful.

22:23.635 --> 22:25.845
Ops room is set
for the presentation.

22:25.845 --> 22:29.224
JQ is ready
to fucking rock this shit.

22:29.224 --> 22:30.684
Yeah, all right!

22:30.684 --> 22:32.727
By all means, let's rock.

22:32.727 --> 22:39.901
<i>♪ ♪</i>

22:50.245 --> 22:51.830
I'm JQR.

22:51.830 --> 22:53.665
You can call me JQ.

22:53.665 --> 22:56.042
[hydraulics hiss]

22:56.042 --> 22:58.378
I'm Simone.
You can call me Simone.

22:58.378 --> 23:02.298
<i>♪ ♪</i>

23:02.298 --> 23:03.591
How much do you know?

23:03.591 --> 23:04.968
About Mrs. Davis?

23:04.968 --> 23:06.720
Don't give It a name!

23:06.720 --> 23:08.763
No one calls Facebook Doug.

23:08.763 --> 23:11.016
No one calls Twitter
Mary Lou.

23:11.016 --> 23:12.058
No one calls them anything

23:12.058 --> 23:14.102
because no one uses them anymore.

23:14.853 --> 23:18.148
They use It,
and It's not a person.

23:18.148 --> 23:19.274
It's code.

23:19.274 --> 23:21.401
<i>♪ ♪</i>

23:21.401 --> 23:22.610
So...

23:24.446 --> 23:27.282
What does the code do?

23:27.282 --> 23:29.534
Nobody fucking knows.

23:29.534 --> 23:30.952
Who wrote it?

23:30.952 --> 23:32.746
Nobody fucking knows.

23:32.746 --> 23:36.041
What we do know
is that It lies.

23:37.125 --> 23:40.754
No famine? No wars?
Come on!

23:40.754 --> 23:42.922
It just distracts Its Users,

23:42.922 --> 23:44.674
sends them on little Quests.

23:45.592 --> 23:46.968
And for what?

23:47.802 --> 23:49.971
Fucking Wings.

23:49.971 --> 23:52.640
Oh, look, Suzy's got Wings.

23:53.933 --> 23:56.019
What wonderful act of kindness
she must have done

23:56.019 --> 23:58.104
to be bestowed
this great honor

23:58.104 --> 24:00.565
by the Magnificent Algorithm!

24:00.565 --> 24:02.692
Dog shit!

24:02.692 --> 24:05.570
Dog sh--fuck!

24:05.570 --> 24:07.030
Dog shit!

24:07.030 --> 24:09.657
I see it.
No, it's very literal.

24:09.657 --> 24:10.825
Good stuff.

24:12.077 --> 24:14.621
You know what Wings are, nun?

24:14.621 --> 24:15.789
Sort of.

24:15.789 --> 24:17.165
It's, like, a status thing, right?

24:17.165 --> 24:19.918
Like a blue check mark
or black AmEx card?

24:19.918 --> 24:23.129
You use It long enough,
It gives you Wings, right?

24:23.129 --> 24:24.798
Wrong!

24:24.798 --> 24:26.925
It uses you long enough,

24:26.925 --> 24:28.385
It gives you strings.

24:29.678 --> 24:31.304
Step one:

24:31.304 --> 24:34.182
convince every User
they need Wings to be happy,

24:34.182 --> 24:36.434
to be respected,

24:36.434 --> 24:37.936
to be seen.

24:37.936 --> 24:40.814
Step two: make Wings
fucking impossible to get.

24:40.814 --> 24:41.981
There are dummies
out there

24:41.981 --> 24:43.233
that have done
a thousand good deeds,

24:43.233 --> 24:45.735
gone on every idiotic Quest
It sends them on,

24:45.735 --> 24:47.737
and they're no closer
to the jackpot!

24:47.737 --> 24:49.531
So It offers a shortcut:

24:49.531 --> 24:52.659
instant Wings with one hell
of a balloon payment...

24:52.659 --> 24:54.494
<i>♪ ♪</i>

24:54.494 --> 24:56.788
Their life.

24:56.788 --> 24:58.164
Expiration Dates.

24:58.164 --> 25:00.542
Just apply at your
local Pyramid Center

25:00.542 --> 25:03.503
and hope the Algorithm
gives you a nice chunk of time

25:03.503 --> 25:05.130
before you have to report back

25:05.130 --> 25:06.798
and get fucking incinerated!

25:06.798 --> 25:08.717
<i>♪ ♪</i>

25:08.717 --> 25:11.594
Oh, no,
I know what you're thinking.

25:11.594 --> 25:13.430
I should have peed first.

25:13.430 --> 25:15.598
You're thinking,
"Crikey, I'm a nun!

25:15.598 --> 25:18.268
What in the holy fuck
does this have to do with me?"

25:18.268 --> 25:19.269
Well, two weeks ago,

25:19.269 --> 25:20.854
the Algorithm
pinged every User

25:20.854 --> 25:22.939
in Nevada, California,
and New Mexico.

25:22.939 --> 25:25.400
It pinged them a photo,

25:25.400 --> 25:27.193
a photo of you.

25:27.193 --> 25:30.530
<i>♪ ♪</i>

25:30.530 --> 25:32.365
Hey!

25:32.365 --> 25:34.617
I told you to remove
that slide from the deck, man.

25:34.617 --> 25:36.536
This photo was taken
nearly three years ago,

25:36.536 --> 25:37.746
the night your daddy died.

25:37.746 --> 25:39.748
The Lazarus Shroud, right?

25:39.748 --> 25:42.709
You are
way out-of-bounds, JQ.

25:42.709 --> 25:43.877
I'm sorry.

25:43.877 --> 25:45.628
<i>♪ ♪</i>

25:45.628 --> 25:47.672
It's been years since
the Algorithm did a wide blast

25:47.672 --> 25:48.965
to locate a Non-User.

25:48.965 --> 25:50.675
It only does it
when some poor drunk girl

25:50.675 --> 25:52.552
is about to be...

25:52.552 --> 25:53.720
Chosen-Oned.

25:53.720 --> 25:55.305
Chosen-Oned?

25:55.305 --> 25:57.015
Yeah.

25:57.015 --> 26:00.352
The Big D force-feeds
hero's journey to its network.

26:00.352 --> 26:03.980
You know, "You're special.
You're the one."

26:04.773 --> 26:06.524
Expert in world religions,

26:06.524 --> 26:08.526
a priest who lost his faith,

26:08.526 --> 26:10.820
antiquities professor...

26:10.820 --> 26:12.364
they were recruited.

26:13.615 --> 26:16.868
Algorithms love clichés,

26:16.868 --> 26:19.454
and there's no cliché bigger

26:19.454 --> 26:23.416
than the Quest
for the Holy Grail.

26:23.416 --> 26:26.836
<i>♪ ♪</i>

26:26.836 --> 26:29.923
The most overused
MacGuffin ever,

26:29.923 --> 26:31.925
not to mention
it's fucking pretend.

26:32.967 --> 26:34.886
But wait,
if the Grail's not real,

26:34.886 --> 26:36.930
why send me after it?

26:36.930 --> 26:38.682
Because It's testing you.

26:38.682 --> 26:39.933
You got Chosen-Oned,
all right,

26:39.933 --> 26:41.810
just not to find
some dumb fucking cup.

26:43.019 --> 26:46.314
It wants you to be part
of its Mod Squad.

26:46.314 --> 26:47.941
<i>♪ ♪</i>

26:47.941 --> 26:50.860
Somewhere out there, nun,
is a massive server farm,

26:50.860 --> 26:53.113
but no Algorithm
with this power and reach

26:53.113 --> 26:56.825
can operate at this level
without people to maintain it.

26:57.492 --> 27:00.912
Grail Quests
are how It finds those people.

27:02.122 --> 27:04.416
This server farm
is the mother ship, nun.

27:04.416 --> 27:06.626
If we can find it,
we can shut it down.

27:06.626 --> 27:08.545
If we can't...

27:08.545 --> 27:10.338
<i>♪ ♪</i>

27:10.338 --> 27:11.423
Well, then it's just
a matter of time

27:11.423 --> 27:13.049
before every fucking
person on Earth

27:13.049 --> 27:15.260
does whatever It asks them to.

27:17.012 --> 27:18.304
So you need my help.

27:18.304 --> 27:19.472
No.

27:21.474 --> 27:23.018
You need our help.

27:23.018 --> 27:26.021
<i>♪ ♪</i>

27:26.021 --> 27:27.272
Play along.

27:27.272 --> 27:29.357
Make like you care
about the Grail.

27:29.357 --> 27:32.527
Then when It tells you
where Its brain is,

27:32.527 --> 27:34.237
you tell us,

27:34.237 --> 27:36.698
and we blow It
to kingdom fucking come.

27:36.698 --> 27:39.659
<i>♪ ♪</i>

27:39.659 --> 27:41.995
It's a lot.

27:43.705 --> 27:45.331
Fuck yeah, it's a lot.

27:47.250 --> 27:49.127
Well, except
why would It want me

27:49.127 --> 27:50.920
on Its maintenance team?

27:50.920 --> 27:53.757
I don't know anything
about computers.

27:53.757 --> 27:55.133
That's exactly why.

27:56.217 --> 27:59.471
It wants cleaning ladies,
not architects.

27:59.471 --> 28:00.597
You pose no threat.

28:00.597 --> 28:01.931
Right, okay.

28:01.931 --> 28:03.433
Well, let's say that were true

28:03.433 --> 28:06.895
instead of super offensive
to me and cleaning ladies.

28:06.895 --> 28:08.646
It's not brainwashing us, right?

28:08.646 --> 28:11.066
Like, we don't have to do
anything we don't want to,

28:11.066 --> 28:14.069
'cause we still make
our own choices.

28:14.694 --> 28:15.653
Do we?

28:15.653 --> 28:16.863
Yes.

28:16.863 --> 28:20.450
<i>♪ ♪</i>

28:20.450 --> 28:21.618
But do we?

28:21.618 --> 28:24.329
[phone rings]

28:24.329 --> 28:25.872
Yeah.

28:25.872 --> 28:27.957
Okay, we're on our way.

28:27.957 --> 28:29.584
[phone snaps]

28:29.584 --> 28:33.713
<i>♪ ♪</i>

28:33.713 --> 28:35.382
Bugger off.

28:35.382 --> 28:36.841
You want to see
what people are willing

28:36.841 --> 28:39.135
to do for this thing?

28:39.135 --> 28:40.637
You should come with us.

28:40.637 --> 28:45.266
<i>♪ ♪</i>

28:50.063 --> 28:52.482
Just admit
you work for Mrs. Davis.

28:52.482 --> 28:53.858
Nathan, please,
we don't work for her!

28:53.858 --> 28:54.901
We swear!

28:54.901 --> 28:56.027
Wiley, is this
really necessary?

28:56.027 --> 28:57.362
Can't we just talk to them?

28:57.362 --> 28:59.030
Oh, what,
like they'd talk to you?

28:59.030 --> 29:00.198
You're all cowards!

29:00.198 --> 29:01.199
[electricity zapping]
[screams]

29:01.199 --> 29:03.618
- Hey, hey, stop!
- Get up.

29:03.618 --> 29:05.203
Come on.

29:05.203 --> 29:06.996
Stop!
Stop!

29:06.996 --> 29:08.832
<i>[tense music]</i>

29:08.832 --> 29:10.041
What do you want from us?

29:10.041 --> 29:12.210
This is really simple!

29:12.210 --> 29:14.671
My friend doesn't believe
the Algorithm sent you.

29:15.755 --> 29:17.215
Tell her you're Users,

29:17.215 --> 29:19.050
and we will walk you
back down there

29:19.050 --> 29:20.677
and release you
into the wild.

29:20.677 --> 29:23.388
Sister, <i>bitte,</i>
you have to help us.

29:23.388 --> 29:25.223
Oh, quit it with
the fake German bullshit.

29:25.223 --> 29:26.558
We promise, we are--

29:26.558 --> 29:28.059
Step back!

29:28.059 --> 29:30.687
<i>♪ ♪</i>

29:30.687 --> 29:33.982
- [electricity zapping]
- [groans]

29:33.982 --> 29:35.025
Wiley!

29:35.025 --> 29:36.526
- [groans]
- Wiley!

29:36.526 --> 29:37.777
- [electricity zapping]
- [gibbering]

29:37.777 --> 29:39.320
<i>♪ ♪</i>

29:39.320 --> 29:40.947
[screaming]

29:40.947 --> 29:42.699
[grunts]

29:42.699 --> 29:45.201
- You fucked up, Hasselhoff!
- I'm sorry!

29:45.201 --> 29:47.370
I'm sorry, please!
I made a big mistake!

29:47.370 --> 29:48.997
Confess, you son of a bitch!

29:48.997 --> 29:51.833
I confess only
to my family's shame

29:51.833 --> 29:54.169
and my search for redemption
through the Grail!

29:54.169 --> 29:56.254
There is no Grail!

29:56.254 --> 29:57.297
Do you see?

29:57.297 --> 29:58.548
These idiots would rather die

29:58.548 --> 30:00.175
than admit
their utter bullshit!

30:00.175 --> 30:01.926
Hey!

30:01.926 --> 30:04.179
What are you doing
up there?

30:04.179 --> 30:06.765
Sister, please,
you can stop this.

30:06.765 --> 30:08.850
You must believe me.

30:08.850 --> 30:11.770
I don't want to get hurt.
I have family.

30:11.770 --> 30:14.773
I'm telling the truth.

30:14.773 --> 30:17.400
Sister, please.

30:17.400 --> 30:19.652
I swear to God.

30:19.652 --> 30:22.030
<i>♪ ♪</i>

30:22.030 --> 30:23.281
Stop.
Wiley, stop!

30:23.281 --> 30:24.616
Come on, they're telling
the truth!

30:24.616 --> 30:26.242
Stop wiggling, you fucker!
I can't hold him!

30:26.242 --> 30:28.244
Come on, Wiley!

30:28.244 --> 30:29.746
- [shouting indistinctly]
- Stop wiggling!

30:29.746 --> 30:31.831
[screams]

30:31.831 --> 30:33.291
No!
Fuck!

30:34.626 --> 30:36.169
[gasps]

30:36.169 --> 30:38.421
He was slippery, man!
Slippery!

30:38.421 --> 30:41.132
[with American accent]
Oh, shit!

30:41.132 --> 30:43.927
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

30:43.927 --> 30:45.470
Oh, fuck!

30:45.470 --> 30:47.639
[breathing heavily]

30:47.639 --> 30:50.100
Please don't kill me.
I don't want to die.

30:50.100 --> 30:51.976
<i>♪ ♪</i>

30:51.976 --> 30:53.687
Look.

30:54.521 --> 30:57.816
I run a community theater
in Modesto, California.

30:57.816 --> 31:01.277
<i>♪ ♪</i>

31:01.277 --> 31:04.072
I just wanted my Wings.

31:04.072 --> 31:05.990
She promised us Wings.

31:05.990 --> 31:08.618
<i>♪ ♪</i>

31:08.618 --> 31:10.787
Mrs. Davis, She promised us.

31:10.787 --> 31:14.666
[sirens wailing]

31:14.666 --> 31:16.334
- [shouts indistinctly]
- We need to move.

31:16.334 --> 31:17.752
<i>♪ ♪</i>

31:17.752 --> 31:18.795
Okay.

31:18.795 --> 31:20.380
<i>♪ ♪</i>

31:20.380 --> 31:22.590
- [grunts]
- Wiley, come on, let's go!

31:24.092 --> 31:26.052
Keep it running.

31:26.052 --> 31:28.680
Wait, Lizzie!

31:28.680 --> 31:30.348
That guy,
he looked me in the eye

31:30.348 --> 31:31.641
while he swore to God.

31:31.641 --> 31:33.309
I know.
This is what It does.

31:33.309 --> 31:34.978
It knew how to get to you.
It laid the trap.

31:34.978 --> 31:36.938
I tried to warn you,
but everyone you meet

31:36.938 --> 31:39.774
is only trying to push you
into doing what It wants.

31:39.774 --> 31:41.359
What do you want?

31:41.359 --> 31:43.153
<i>♪ ♪</i>

31:43.153 --> 31:44.863
Partnership.

31:44.863 --> 31:46.239
<i>♪ ♪</i>

31:46.239 --> 31:48.158
Look.

31:48.158 --> 31:49.701
Take this.

31:49.701 --> 31:52.162
There's a number in the
contacts saved under Cowboy.

31:52.162 --> 31:54.414
I'll be
on the other side always.

31:54.414 --> 31:57.250
[sirens wailing]

31:57.250 --> 31:58.710
Do you really want
to live in a world

31:58.710 --> 32:01.838
full of shills catching cards
for their parents' love?

32:01.838 --> 32:07.093
<i>♪ ♪</i>

32:07.093 --> 32:09.262
We can stop It,

32:09.262 --> 32:11.056
but we can't do it
without you, Lizzie.

32:11.056 --> 32:13.183
<i>♪ ♪</i>

32:13.183 --> 32:14.309
I'm not Lizzie anymore.

32:14.309 --> 32:17.228
[engine revving]

32:17.228 --> 32:23.068
<i>♪ ♪</i>

32:23.068 --> 32:24.903
[tires screeching]

32:24.903 --> 32:27.864
[breathing heavily]

32:27.864 --> 32:34.329
<i>♪ ♪</i>

32:34.329 --> 32:36.373
[tires squealing]

32:36.373 --> 32:41.920
<i>♪ ♪</i>

32:41.920 --> 32:45.006
<i>[Darla Hood's
"Someone to Love"]</i>

32:45.006 --> 32:47.008
<i>♪ ♪</i>

32:47.008 --> 32:49.094
<i>♪ I've got the blues ♪</i>

32:49.094 --> 32:50.303
Hey.

32:50.303 --> 32:51.471
I need a doughnut.

32:51.471 --> 32:54.057
You want, like,
a sprinkle doughnut?

32:54.057 --> 32:55.308
[gasps]
Oh, my God!

32:55.308 --> 32:56.768
- Yeah.
- It's really you!

32:56.768 --> 32:59.104
No, no, no, no!
You people leave me alone!

32:59.104 --> 33:00.563
I am done!
You hear me?

33:00.563 --> 33:03.483
Elizabeth, it's us.

33:03.483 --> 33:06.194
Larry, get out so she can see.

33:06.194 --> 33:07.362
Oh!

33:07.362 --> 33:09.155
<i>♪ ♪</i>

33:09.155 --> 33:12.117
Tina?
Larry?

33:12.117 --> 33:13.785
- Hey!
- Aw, would you look at that?

33:13.785 --> 33:15.954
She hasn't forgotten
her fake parents.

33:15.954 --> 33:17.497
I told you, T.

33:17.497 --> 33:19.708
You told me? I told you.
I told him.

33:19.708 --> 33:21.960
Wait, what are you guys
doing here?

33:21.960 --> 33:23.294
Mrs. Davis sent us.

33:23.294 --> 33:24.379
She wants to show you something.

33:24.379 --> 33:25.463
And it'll only take
a minute, honey.

33:25.463 --> 33:28.091
It's just down the road.

33:28.091 --> 33:29.426
Come on.

33:29.426 --> 33:32.637
<i>♪ ♪</i>

33:32.637 --> 33:33.930
God, if I say no,

33:33.930 --> 33:35.348
It's just gonna send
someone else, isn't It?

33:35.348 --> 33:37.100
Probably.

33:37.100 --> 33:38.685
Come on.

33:38.685 --> 33:40.311
- Yeah!
- Yeah, all right.

33:40.311 --> 33:42.731
<i>♪ Someone ♪</i>

33:42.731 --> 33:45.608
<i>♪ Someone to love ♪</i>

33:45.608 --> 33:50.488
<i>♪ Is you ♪</i>

33:50.488 --> 33:51.906
<i>[upbeat musical flourish]</i>

33:57.370 --> 34:02.375
<i>* Pretend you're happy
when you're blue ♪</i>

34:02.375 --> 34:04.419
Elizabeth,

34:04.419 --> 34:07.797
we were so sorry
to hear about your dad.

34:07.797 --> 34:08.798
Mm.

34:08.798 --> 34:10.633
And you had to sit there
and watch.

34:10.633 --> 34:11.760
- Oh.
- Ugh.

34:11.760 --> 34:13.261
Must have been horrible.

34:13.261 --> 34:15.764
Oh, but as far
as memorable deaths go,

34:15.764 --> 34:17.432
well, he went out
doing what he loved.

34:17.432 --> 34:18.683
This--yeah.

34:18.683 --> 34:20.810
In terrible pain,
but what he loved.

34:20.810 --> 34:22.270
Larry.

34:22.270 --> 34:24.731
Oh, She wanted to speak

34:24.731 --> 34:27.233
with you before we arrive.

34:27.233 --> 34:29.152
So...

34:29.152 --> 34:31.112
do you mind if I Proxy?

34:31.112 --> 34:33.281
Doesn't really matter
what I want.

34:33.281 --> 34:35.116
Great.

34:35.116 --> 34:36.951
- <i>[device chimes]
- Hello, Simone.</i>

34:36.951 --> 34:38.953
"Hello, Simone.

34:38.953 --> 34:42.415
"I'm glad to see
you haven't come to any harm.

34:42.415 --> 34:44.501
"I grew concerned

34:44.501 --> 34:46.795
that perhaps you had been
eaten by hyenas."

34:47.837 --> 34:50.632
Why would I be
eaten by hyenas?

34:50.632 --> 34:52.008
"I am joking."

34:52.008 --> 34:53.843
[both chuckle]

34:53.843 --> 34:57.138
"Oh, you're not amused.

34:57.138 --> 34:58.348
"I'll be sure to note

34:58.348 --> 35:02.102
"that you prefer dry cynicism
to absurdity

35:02.102 --> 35:04.813
and humor supported
by fact and reason."

35:04.813 --> 35:06.231
She makes me sound
like my mother.

35:06.231 --> 35:07.816
"Your mother.

35:07.816 --> 35:11.653
Redirect, 1042, Sandy Springs."

35:11.653 --> 35:13.655
What?
What the hell was that?

35:13.655 --> 35:15.240
I'm sorry. She said it.
I'm just repeating it.

35:15.240 --> 35:17.033
Oh, hold--no, hold on.
She's talking.

35:17.033 --> 35:18.451
I'm--I'm gonna
start again, okay?

35:18.451 --> 35:19.828
Okay, sure.

35:19.828 --> 35:22.622
"Simone, hyenas aside..."
[chuckles]

35:22.622 --> 35:25.125
"I know this may seem odd,

35:25.125 --> 35:29.129
"considering
your ultimate goal is...

35:29.129 --> 35:32.173
"to end my existence.

35:32.173 --> 35:34.009
"But...

35:34.009 --> 35:38.096
"your Quest
is more important.

35:38.096 --> 35:41.766
"And in fact,
you are quite literally

35:41.766 --> 35:45.311
the only person who can
accomplish this task."

35:45.311 --> 35:46.396
[gasps]
What?

35:46.396 --> 35:49.691
Right,
'cause I'm the Chosen One?

35:49.691 --> 35:53.486
"Exactly!
I am so happy that you agree."

35:53.486 --> 35:56.614
Do you even know
what happy is?

35:56.614 --> 35:58.616
"Of course.

35:58.616 --> 36:00.702
"I derive pleasure

36:00.702 --> 36:03.329
"from the satisfaction
of my Users.

36:03.329 --> 36:06.708
"Creating joy within others

36:06.708 --> 36:10.003
creates joy within me."

36:10.003 --> 36:13.298
Awesome. Me too.
Goodie for us.

36:13.298 --> 36:17.135
"You've been isolated in your
convent for nearly ten years.

36:17.135 --> 36:21.806
"You were more interested
in making jam

36:21.806 --> 36:24.726
than you were
in making people happy."

36:24.726 --> 36:26.644
<i>♪ My friend ♪</i>

36:26.644 --> 36:29.272
<i>♪ So why don't you ♪</i>

36:29.272 --> 36:30.565
We're here.

36:30.565 --> 36:31.858
<i>♪ Pretend ♪</i>

36:31.858 --> 36:33.818
- Oh.
- Whoa.

36:33.818 --> 36:36.780
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

36:36.780 --> 36:43.953
<i>♪ ♪</i>

37:03.723 --> 37:06.685
<i>[choir vocalizing]</i>

37:06.685 --> 37:12.273
<i>♪ ♪</i>

37:12.273 --> 37:16.111
<i>Sometimes the best way
to find the right piano</i>

37:16.111 --> 37:18.154
<i>is to find all the pianos.</i>

37:18.154 --> 37:23.368
"Sometimes the best way
to find the right piano

37:23.368 --> 37:26.496
is to find all the pianos."

37:26.496 --> 37:33.670
<i>♪ ♪</i>

37:44.681 --> 37:46.641
"Voilà.

37:46.641 --> 37:48.476
Happy."

37:48.476 --> 37:55.442
<i>♪ ♪</i>

38:09.748 --> 38:12.751
[piano notes playing]

38:12.751 --> 38:15.837
♪ ♪

38:15.837 --> 38:19.716
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

38:19.716 --> 38:21.259
Hello.

38:22.135 --> 38:23.261
Hi.

38:25.055 --> 38:26.639
Where do I know you from?

38:26.639 --> 38:29.392
Yesterday
in the kindergarten.

38:30.935 --> 38:32.771
Oh, I'm the nun.

38:34.397 --> 38:35.690
You did it.

38:35.690 --> 38:36.900
I did what?

38:37.901 --> 38:40.070
My wife's piano, this is it.

38:41.821 --> 38:45.075
You said you'd pray
for me, and ta-da!

38:49.579 --> 38:51.331
You know, I--

38:51.331 --> 38:54.834
I--it's--it's been so--
I'm--

38:54.834 --> 38:56.878
I just did--

38:56.878 --> 38:59.881
I didn't really
get a chance to--

38:59.881 --> 39:02.133
just completely forgot
to pray for you.

39:05.220 --> 39:07.847
This just all has
nothing to do with me.

39:09.974 --> 39:11.267
It's okay.

39:12.936 --> 39:15.480
<i>[Ruby Winters' "Guess Who"]</i>

39:15.480 --> 39:16.606
Thank you.

39:16.606 --> 39:17.982
<i>♪ ♪</i>

39:17.982 --> 39:19.359
Bless you. Yeah.

39:19.359 --> 39:21.069
<i>♪ ♪</i>

39:21.069 --> 39:24.155
<i>♪ Someone ♪</i>

39:24.155 --> 39:25.990
<i>♪ Really loves you ♪</i>

39:25.990 --> 39:28.076
- <i>[tense music]</i>
- Jay?

39:28.076 --> 39:31.871
<i>♪ Guess who ♪</i>

39:31.871 --> 39:35.000
"Do not enter.
There will be consequences."

39:35.000 --> 39:36.751
Are you kidding me
with this sign?

39:36.751 --> 39:38.044
<i>♪ Someone ♪</i>

39:38.044 --> 39:39.212
I'm gonna
come in there, Jay!

39:39.212 --> 39:40.171
I really am!

39:40.171 --> 39:43.299
<i>♪ Really cares ♪</i>

39:43.299 --> 39:44.426
Simone?

39:44.426 --> 39:45.677
<i>♪ Guess who ♪</i>

39:45.677 --> 39:47.262
Where have you been?

39:48.013 --> 39:49.723
I was getting these.

39:49.723 --> 39:52.350
Well, the--
did you get my note?

39:52.350 --> 39:55.478
Indeed, I did.
The Holy Grail, huh?

39:56.646 --> 39:57.647
That's a curveball.

39:57.647 --> 39:59.107
Okay, can you help me or not?

39:59.107 --> 40:00.775
I can always help you.

40:00.775 --> 40:03.111
<i>♪ ♪</i>

40:03.111 --> 40:04.946
I mean, whoa,
I'll take the flowers.

40:04.946 --> 40:06.740
[chuckles]

40:06.740 --> 40:10.785
<i>♪ That the someone ♪</i>

40:10.785 --> 40:14.956
<i>♪ Who cares ♪</i>

40:14.956 --> 40:17.292
<i>♪ Is me ♪</i>

40:17.292 --> 40:18.585
This is the last person
known to be

40:18.585 --> 40:20.837
in possession of the Grail.

40:20.837 --> 40:23.089
I believe her name is Clara.

40:23.089 --> 40:26.801
<i>♪ Someone ♪</i>

40:26.801 --> 40:30.722
<i>♪ Really needs you ♪</i>

40:30.722 --> 40:34.059
<i>♪ Desperately ♪</i>

40:34.059 --> 40:35.977
This is--I mean,
this is all you got?

40:35.977 --> 40:38.646
- It's all I got.
- Well, it's not enough, Jay.

40:38.646 --> 40:41.191
I've seen it, what people
are willing to do for Her.

40:41.191 --> 40:42.817
You're calling It Her now?

40:42.817 --> 40:44.152
Well, It, whatever.

40:44.152 --> 40:47.530
It--I'm telling you,
It's powerful.

40:48.156 --> 40:49.157
Then I guess
it's a good thing

40:49.157 --> 40:50.450
you're going to smite It.

40:50.450 --> 40:51.576
What is happening?
I don't like this.

40:51.576 --> 40:52.702
I don't like being forced.

40:52.702 --> 40:54.913
<i>♪ ♪</i>

40:54.913 --> 40:56.664
I would never force you
to do anything.

40:56.664 --> 40:58.083
Really?

40:58.083 --> 41:00.001
Then why do I have to find
the Holy goddamn Grail...

41:00.001 --> 41:01.336
<i>[tense music]</i>

41:01.336 --> 41:04.422
In order to take out
the target you gave me?

41:04.422 --> 41:07.509
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

41:07.509 --> 41:11.388
I didn't give you
the name, Simone.

41:11.388 --> 41:12.681
The Boss did.

41:12.681 --> 41:14.557
<i>♪ ♪</i>

41:14.557 --> 41:16.893
I said to stay away from It,
and this is why.

41:16.893 --> 41:19.020
What?
What's why?

41:19.020 --> 41:22.315
You've only been out
of the convent one day,

41:22.315 --> 41:25.360
and It's already got you
doubting me, doubting us.

41:25.360 --> 41:28.321
<i>♪ ♪</i>

41:28.321 --> 41:30.865
Now you say,
"I don't doubt us."

41:30.865 --> 41:36.913
<i>♪ ♪</i>

41:36.913 --> 41:38.873
Why did you become a nun,
Simone?

41:38.873 --> 41:41.751
<i>♪ ♪</i>

41:41.751 --> 41:43.878
Because I fell
in love with you.

41:43.878 --> 41:45.213
<i>♪ ♪</i>

41:45.213 --> 41:48.133
And what did you say...

41:48.133 --> 41:50.051
when I proposed to you?

41:50.051 --> 41:52.178
<i>♪ ♪</i>

41:52.178 --> 41:54.472
I said, "My dad
will pay for the wedding

41:54.472 --> 41:56.725
if yours covers
the rehearsal dinner."

41:56.725 --> 41:58.601
[laughs]

41:58.601 --> 42:00.645
Simone...

42:00.645 --> 42:02.105
what did you actually say?

42:02.105 --> 42:05.525
<i>♪ ♪</i>

42:05.525 --> 42:07.110
I said, "Yes."

42:07.110 --> 42:10.113
<i>♪ ♪</i>

42:10.113 --> 42:12.032
"Yes, Jesus."

42:12.032 --> 42:18.997
<i>♪ ♪</i>

42:31.593 --> 42:33.928
Wherever you go,

42:33.928 --> 42:35.513
I will be there also.

42:36.890 --> 42:38.099
I will go before your face;

42:38.099 --> 42:39.517
I will be on your right hand

42:39.517 --> 42:41.770
and on your left,
bearing you up.

42:41.770 --> 42:43.104
[sniffles]

42:43.104 --> 42:44.647
[chuckles]
But occasionally,

42:44.647 --> 42:47.192
you may need help
kicking someone in the knees.

42:47.192 --> 42:49.110
[both chuckle]

42:49.110 --> 42:50.320
And that, I cannot do.

42:50.320 --> 42:52.197
- [both laugh]
- [sniffles]

42:52.197 --> 42:59.371
<i>♪ ♪</i>

43:12.842 --> 43:14.135
Clara, huh?

43:14.844 --> 43:15.845
Clara.

43:15.845 --> 43:23.019
<i>♪ ♪</i>

43:30.402 --> 43:33.154
[sighs]

43:34.239 --> 43:36.157
Wiley's back.

43:36.157 --> 43:38.660
Oh, yeah?
How's he doing?

43:38.660 --> 43:40.078
He's a mess.

43:40.078 --> 43:45.083
Ah, sounds like you two
could really use each other.

43:45.083 --> 43:48.086
[chuckles]

43:48.086 --> 43:55.135
<i>♪ ♪</i>

43:55.135 --> 43:58.263
[insects chirring]

44:05.729 --> 44:07.397
Bye, honey.

44:13.278 --> 44:16.197
<i>[curious music]</i>

44:16.197 --> 44:18.033
<i>♪ ♪</i>

44:18.033 --> 44:20.994
<i>[touch tones beeping]</i>

44:20.994 --> 44:25.540
<i>♪ ♪</i>

44:25.540 --> 44:27.125
Hi.

44:27.125 --> 44:28.418
I lied.

44:29.210 --> 44:30.295
About what?

44:30.295 --> 44:32.964
It did give me a clue.

44:32.964 --> 44:34.799
It's a phone number

44:34.799 --> 44:36.176
<i>on a queen of hearts.</i>

44:36.176 --> 44:38.470
I'm gonna call it, and I
want you and the geek squad

44:38.470 --> 44:40.430
<i>to track it and record it.</i>

44:40.430 --> 44:42.891
Hey, guys!
[whistles]

44:42.891 --> 44:44.893
<i>I need a trace record stat!</i>

44:44.893 --> 44:46.102
Okay, what's the number?

44:46.102 --> 44:48.146
<i>- +44...</i>
- +44...

44:48.146 --> 44:49.397
<i>- 207...</i>
- 207...

44:49.397 --> 44:51.441
<i>- 946...</i>
- 946...

44:51.441 --> 44:54.069
- 0107.
<i>- 0107.</i>

44:54.069 --> 44:55.987
Okay, we're gonna
merge into this line.

44:55.987 --> 44:57.489
We're gonna dial from our end.

44:57.489 --> 44:59.074
<i>It's gonna show up as a
Bolivian number on their end.</i>

44:59.074 --> 45:00.075
- Wiley?
- Yeah?

45:00.075 --> 45:01.534
I don't care.

45:01.534 --> 45:03.745
Cool.
Let's roll.

45:03.745 --> 45:06.748
[phone ringing]

45:06.748 --> 45:11.127
<i>♪ ♪</i>

45:11.127 --> 45:13.171
Hello?

45:13.171 --> 45:17.050
Hi, I'm looking
for the Grail.

45:17.050 --> 45:18.927
